School Management Portal Backend
Welcome to the backend of the School Management Portal, a robust and scalable server-side application developed in JavaScript. This backend powers the administrative functionalities of the school management system, facilitating efficient handling of staff registrations, student records, and academic results.

Key Features
Staff Management: :

Manage staff registrations and profiles.
Student Results Management:

Upload and manage student academic results.
How to Use
Setup and Installation:

Clone the repository: git clone <repository-url>
Navigate to the project directory: cd school-management-backend
Install dependencies: npm install
Environment Configuration:

Create a .env file in the root directory with the following format:
MONGO_URI=your_mongo_db_connection_string
PORT=your_desired_port_number
JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret_key
Replace the placeholders with your actual configuration values.
Running the Server:

Start the server: npm start
The backend will be accessible at http://localhost:<PORT>.
API Endpoints:

The endpoints for managing staff and student results are self-explanatory and can be found in the codebase.
Use tools like Postman for testing the API endpoints.
Technologies Used
Node.js: For building the server-side application.
Express.js: For handling routing and middleware.
MongoDB: For database management.
Mongoose: For MongoDB object modeling.
Note
This backend is still a work in progress but is fully functional for key features.
Comprehensive documentation for all API endpoints is available in the project repository.